---
block_id: 029
name: hub-firewall-policies
display_name: "Hub Firewall Policies"
version: 1.1.0
category: core
device_role: hub
vendor: fortinet
platform: fortigate
min_fortios: "7.4.0"

description: |
  Firewall policies for SD-WAN hub. Allows traffic between overlay, LAN,
  and WAN interfaces. Based on production hub configuration.

  CRITICAL: Uses edit 0 for auto-assign policy IDs to avoid overwriting
  existing policies. Verify by policy NAME, not ID.

  KEY POLICIES:
  - SDWAN_Overlay_Traffic: Hub loopback + overlay bidirectional
  - SDWAN_OL_To_Port2: Overlay to LAN (NAT for spoke access to hub LAN)
  - SDWAN-BGP-LOOPBACK: Overlay to BGP_Lo (spoke BGP sessions)
  - BGP-TO-SDWAN: BGP_Lo to overlay (hub BGP replies)
  - SDWAN-to-INET: Overlay to WAN (spoke internet breakout via hub)

  SECURITY NOTE: No WAN_to_LAN policy - this would expose hub LAN to internet.

depends_on:
  - block_id: 027
    reason: "SD-WAN zone must exist"
  - block_id: 022
    reason: "LAN, WAN, Hub_Lo, and BGP_Lo interfaces must exist"

provides:
  - hub-firewall-policies
  - hub-overlay-routing
  - hub-bgp-loopback-policies

parameters:
  - name: LAN_INTERFACE
    description: "LAN interface name"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "port2"

  - name: WAN_INTERFACE
    description: "WAN interface name"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "port1"

  - name: ZONE_NAME
    description: "SD-WAN zone name"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "SDWAN_OVERLAY"

  - name: HUB_LOOPBACK
    description: "Hub loopback interface name"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "Hub_Lo"

  - name: BGP_LOOPBACK
    description: "BGP loopback interface name"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "BGP_Lo"

verification:
  commands:
    - "show firewall policy | grep -A2 'set name'"
  expected_patterns:
    - 'name "SDWAN_Overlay_Traffic"'
    - 'name "SDWAN_OL_To_Port2"'
    - 'name "SDWAN-BGP-LOOPBACK"'
    - 'name "BGP-TO-SDWAN"'
    - 'name "SDWAN-to-INET"'
  note: |
    Verify by policy NAME not ID. IDs are auto-assigned and may vary.

rollback:
  note: |
    Rollback must delete by name, not ID. IDs vary per deployment.
    Run these commands manually or via CLI script:
  commands:
    - "config firewall policy"
    - 'delete "SDWAN_Overlay_Traffic"'
    - 'delete "SDWAN_OL_To_Port2"'
    - 'delete "SDWAN-BGP-LOOPBACK"'
    - 'delete "BGP-TO-SDWAN"'
    - 'delete "SDWAN-to-INET"'
    - "end"
  warning: |
    FortiOS delete command may require policy ID, not name.
    Query IDs first: get firewall policy | grep -B1 "name.*SDWAN"

notes: |
  GPOT FIXES (v1.1.0):
  - Changed from fixed IDs (1-6) to edit 0 (auto-assign) to avoid overwriting
  - REMOVED dangerous WAN_to_LAN policy (allow-all from WAN to LAN)
  - REMOVED LAN_to_WAN policy (not needed for hub - spokes don't route via hub LAN)
  - ADDED BGP loopback policies for spoke BGP sessions
  - ADDED Hub_Lo in overlay traffic policy for hub services
  - Verification now uses policy names, not IDs
  - Based on production hub howard-sdwan-hub-1 (192.168.215.15)

---

config firewall policy
    edit 0
        set name "SDWAN_Overlay_Traffic"
        set srcintf "{{HUB_LOOPBACK}}" "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        set dstintf "{{HUB_LOOPBACK}}" "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        set action accept
        set srcaddr "all"
        set dstaddr "all"
        set schedule "always"
        set service "ALL"
        set logtraffic all
        set comments "Hub loopback + overlay bidirectional - spoke-to-spoke via hub"
    next
    edit 0
        set name "SDWAN_OL_To_Port2"
        set srcintf "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        set dstintf "{{LAN_INTERFACE}}"
        set action accept
        set srcaddr "all"
        set dstaddr "all"
        set schedule "always"
        set service "ALL"
        set logtraffic all
        set nat enable
        set comments "Spoke access to hub LAN resources"
    next
    edit 0
        set name "SDWAN-BGP-LOOPBACK"
        set srcintf "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        set dstintf "{{BGP_LOOPBACK}}"
        set action accept
        set srcaddr "all"
        set dstaddr "all"
        set schedule "always"
        set service "ALL"
        set comments "Spoke BGP sessions to hub BGP loopback"
    next
    edit 0
        set name "BGP-TO-SDWAN"
        set srcintf "{{BGP_LOOPBACK}}"
        set dstintf "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        set action accept
        set srcaddr "all"
        set dstaddr "all"
        set schedule "always"
        set service "ALL"
        set comments "Hub BGP replies to spokes"
    next
    edit 0
        set name "SDWAN-to-INET"
        set srcintf "{{ZONE_NAME}}"
        set dstintf "{{WAN_INTERFACE}}"
        set action accept
        set srcaddr "all"
        set dstaddr "all"
        set schedule "always"
        set service "ALL"
        set logtraffic all
        set nat enable
        set comments "Spoke internet breakout via hub (central breakout)"
    next
end
